	<exercise>
		<!-- variant consists of 3 "flags" connected by '_' (underscore)
			   1st flag is whether a side should be computed or a chunk of a side, or (oneside/onechunk/onerandom/twosides/twochunks/onesideonechunk/tworandom/random)
			   2d flag is whether all lengths values will be displayed or only two couples of values (random/all/twocouples)
				 /!\ if 1st value belongs to twosides/twochunks/onesideonechunk/tworandom or if random leads to one of these, then 2d value will be automatically considered as 'all'
				 3d flag is whether two lengths should be added to get another, at some point, or not (false/true/random)
			   Default values (if variant is not here) will be as if variant="oneside_random_false"
			   It's also impossible to ask to calculate the two chunks (so display all lengths available)
			   and in the same time to require an "additive" version of the exercise (1st flag true),
			   so this case will be automatically removed. -->
		<question kind="intercept_theorem" subkind="triangle" variant="oneside_all_false">
			<nb source="ext_proportionality_quadruplet_11to30">1</nb>
		</question>
	</exercise>

	<exercise>
